						<summary>

						<p>Stone pedestal bearing foot-marks kept near the house of Taṭṭimaniyavaru.</p>						

						<p>Amōghavarsha (undated).</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription belongs to the reign of Amōghavarsha. Refers to the foot-marks <hi rend="italic">(pāduke)</hi> and worship of the feet of the <hi rend="italic">guru.</hi> Mentions <hi rend="italic">paṭṭagāṟa</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">gāvuṇḍa</hi> of Uṇkal-30. It is in characters of about the 9th century A.D. </p>						

						</summary>
